Text.Value: Be quick!
Another word from you and you'll fly out of this tower.
Attack.
Enter freely. You are welcome.
You are intruding in the palace of Cazador Szarr. Leave now, citizen.
The master needs no 'inspections'. The master sees all.
*She doesn't say a word. In fact, she barely seems there at all.*
You will be brought to the master. You will answer for your blasphemy.
The master did not mention you.
*The guard's words are clear, but spoken without thought or intent. Behind her eyes you see - nothing. She's a drone under some magical charm.*
I'll hurry up.
You'll be free of 'the master' soon. I'll see to that.
Attack.
Hurry, the palace is being sealed. You must not be late. You must not anger the master.
My life belongs to the master. I live and die in his service.
*She pauses for a moment, but keeps her mouth shut. It seems you're free to enter.*
It is the Ascension - the master expects all his children to attend. You must not be late.
Cazador hired me for a job - it's very hush, hush. If you don't let me in, he's going to be most upset.
You cannot be here - it is forbidden.
All right, I'll go.
This is the palace of Cazador Szarr. Entry is forbidden. Leave now, citizen.
Of course, whatever the master desires.
Free of the master? But the master is freedom. The master is everything.
Leave, citizen.
Master Astarion? But the time is almost here - you should be at the ritual.
Enter freely and of your own will.
This place is forbidden. Leave.

EditorData.NodeContext: Stressing the last word as a threat

Text.Value: *The guard's words are clear, but spoken without thought or intent. Behind her eyes you see - nothing. She must be one of the charmed thralls Astarion mentioned.*
What ritual are you talking about?
Blasphemy against the master! Blasphemy!
Our master awaits. Go!
Protect the palace! Protect the master's sanctuary!
I am inspecting the security, on your master's orders.
I'm here to kill Cazador Szarr.

Synopsis:
Main guard's dialog in Guard Tower in Cazador's Palace.
Triggered automatically when you enter the tower, but also can be triggered by clicking on the guard. 
Guard is a female dwarf mesmerised to do the bidding of a powerful vampire. She speaks in a slightly dreamy tone.
